#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:2
msgid "Minimal Measures"
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:4
msgid ""
"***As a general rule, we encourage conference organizers to implement all "
"the üçé measures and at least one of the ‚úÖ suggestions.***"
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:6
msgid ""
"Making your conference inclusive and encouraging diversity is a breeze!"
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:8
msgid "What are the easiest and most impactful measures?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:10
msgid ""
"Just follow the measures below. The are explained in more depth in the other"
" pages of this Cookbook. Measures that are **easy to implement** and have a "
"**strong positive impact** are &quot;low-hanging fruit&quot; and marked with"
" a red apple emoji: üçé. Measures that take more effort but have considerable "
"impact are marked with a green checkmark: ‚úÖ."
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:13
msgid "[Organizing Committee](03_organizing_committee.md)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:14
msgid ""
"‚úÖ The organizing committee itself should reflect the diversity you want to "
"create in your conference!  Prioritizing diversity starts with you."
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:17
msgid ""
"Conference chairs and lead organizers should take special care to recruit an"
" organizing committee that reflects the diversity of the event you aspire to"
" create."
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:19
msgid "[Venue Selection &amp; On-Site Services](04_venue_selection.md)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:21
msgid "Accessibility Considerations"
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:23
msgid "Consider attendees who may need accommodations for a disability"
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:26
msgid "Mobility"
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:28
msgid ""
"üçé Reserve seats in rooms for folks who might need it (wheelchair, crutches, "
"cane, etc.). Choose easily-accessible seats, such as at the end of a row on "
"the aisle."
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:30
msgid ""
"üçé Create wide aisles between chairs to make it easier for people who are "
"mobility-impaired to navigate the room."
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:33
msgid "Disability"
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:35
msgid ""
"üçé Provide large-text signs and easy-to-read maps. Ask conference organizers "
"to announce important information over the microphone, which helps people "
"with impaired vision."
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:37
msgid ""
"‚úÖ Book sign-language interpreters and/or real-time captioning (someone "
"typing captions) for deaf and hard-of-hearing attendees.**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:40
msgid "Bathrooms"
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:42
msgid "Gender-Neutral Bathrooms"
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:44
msgid ""
"üçé Post signs in the restroom and/or on the door instructing what to do if "
"you think someone is in the \"wrong\" restroom"
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:47
msgid ""
"\"If you think someone's gender doesn't match the sign on the door, please "
"follow these steps: Don't worry about it, they know better than you.\" (via "
"[@LGBTplusBristol](https://twitter.com/lgbtplusbristol))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:49
msgid ""
"‚úÖ Ensuring your conference has easily accessible gender-neutral restrooms is"
" a simple way to help non-binary and trans individuals feel included and "
"welcome at your conference.**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:52
msgid "Toiletries/Supplies"
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:54
msgid ""
"üçé Provide tampons and pads in all restrooms (some people who identify as "
"male have periods and may need them)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:57
msgid "üçé Dedicated rooms"
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:59
msgid ""
"The rooms should be clearly labeled to prevent accidental entry, and their "
"locations should be provided in both the print and the online conference "
"directory and maps."
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:61
msgid ""
"Don't allow anyone (even organizers) to use the room for other purposes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:64
msgid "üçé Nursing & Pumping Room"
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:66
msgid "Ensure there is a dedicated, single-occupancy space with lock."
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:68
msgid "For the room to be optimally useful, these things are desired:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:70
msgid ""
"Locking door, Comfortable chair, a desk or table next to the chair (to set "
"the pump, bottles, etc. on), no more than 4 feet from the nearest electrical"
" outlet, cleaning wipes, paper towels, and a garbage can, masking tape and a"
" marker for labeling milk bottles and pump parts, close proximity to a sink "
"for hand washing and washing of pump parts, a refrigerator for storage of "
"pumped milk  in the pumping room or nearby, dim lighting"
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:72
msgid "üçé Gender-Neutral Bottle Feeding Room"
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:74
msgid ""
"Bottle-fed babies can be fed by caregivers of any gender and also benefit "
"from a quiet, low-distraction, private space for feeding."
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:76
msgid ""
"This should be a separate, additional room ( NOT the same as the nursing and"
" pumping room ) which should be clearly labelled. It could accommodate "
"multiple babies at a time and be equipped with: multiple comfortable chairs "
"with broad armrests to facilitate bottle feeding positions, a bottle warmer,"
" paper towels, cleaning wipes and garbage can for cleanliness, dim lighting "
"and in a quiet area of the conference center/venue"
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:79
msgid "üçé Quiet Room"
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:81
msgid ""
"A dedicated room for people who need a break from the stimulation of being "
"surrounded by people at the conference; no phone calls, talking/socializing,"
" notification beeps! People whose religions require frequent prayer can make"
" use of the quiet room."
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:83
msgid "Consider \"quiet areas\" if a separate room is not possible."
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:85
msgid "[Catering](05_catering.md)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:87
msgid ""
"Making sure that your attendees have something they can eat at mealtimes is "
"an important element of building an inclusive and welcoming conference."
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:89
msgid ""
"Best to have a sign/small label in front of each dish with a list of "
"ingredients and common labels (e.g. \"gluten-free, vegan, includes "
"peanuts\")."
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:92
msgid "üçé Ask your caterer to create and provide the labels."
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:95
msgid ""
"üçé Make sure to include a variety of beverages, in particular non-alcoholic "
"and non-caffeinated."
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:96
msgid ""
"‚úÖ Common dietary needs to plan for: gluten free, dairy free, vegan, "
"vegetarian, pork free, shellfish free, soy free, nut free - especially "
"peanut (this is usually a serious allergy so take extra care), kosher, halal"
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:98
msgid "[Code of Conduct (CoC)](07_code_of_conduct.md)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:100
msgid "Awareness"
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:102
msgid ""
"Make sure that everyone involved in your conference/event is aware that the "
"CoC applies to them: that not only includes participants, but also speakers,"
" sponsors, committee members etc."
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:104
msgid ""
"üçé Tick box at registration that confirms that the participant has read it"
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:106
msgid "üçé Include a copy of the CoC in the sponsor packet"
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:108
msgid ""
"üçé Mention that the CoC applies to the speakers in the speaker guidelines"
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:110
msgid "üçé Ensure that CoC is easily accessible on the conference website"
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:112
msgid "üçé Include a short version on the printed schedule as a reminder"
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:114
msgid ""
"üçé Mention it in the welcome talk and at the start of every day, including "
"who to contact if there is a problem/violation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:117
msgid "[Participant and Speaker Selection](09_participant_selection.md)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:119
msgid "Speakers"
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:121
msgid ""
"üçé Consider the specific wording of how you solicit talks, e.g. call for "
"\"Speakers who have advice or expertise to share\" rather than \"experts in "
"best practices\""
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:123
msgid "Invited Speakers"
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:124
msgid ""
"‚úÖ Reach beyond the conference organizers' own networks. Take steps to go out"
" and find people who might be lesser-known but would make great speakers. "
"Look for more than just \"the usual suspects\" and reach out to your wider "
"network for ideas, suggestions, and introductions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:126
msgid "Selecting Speakers"
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:128
msgid "üçé Call For Proposals instructions -- be clear who you want"
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:130
msgid ""
"In the solicitation, be transparent that you want a broad & diverse group to"
" share their expertise."
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:132
msgid ""
"Let applicants know what criteria will be used to assess their submission "
"and how speakers will be chosen."
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:135
msgid ""
"If your conference has a long history and you're trying to change what it's "
"like, be up front about the kinds of people you want to have speak, why, and"
" how this may look different from years past."
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:138
msgid "Call for Proposals Review"
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:140
msgid ""
"‚úÖ There are many approaches to reviewing and selecting conference "
"contributions and there is no foolproof type of review that always avoids "
"biases. Regardless of which approach you choose, open or anonymized, we "
"encourage you to make it \"double\" so that both parties know each other "
"(double-open) or neither party knows the other (double-closed)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:144
msgid "Attracting Attendees"
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:146
msgid ""
"üçé Pay attention to the photos you use to advertise your event‚Äîwhat do people"
" look like who attend?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:149
msgid "[Event Registration](10_event_registration.md)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:150
msgid "What to ask on your registration form (and what not to ask)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:152
msgid "Preparing to meet accessibility needs"
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:154
msgid ""
"üçé Ask registrants if they have any additional accessibility needs, and if "
"so, provide instructions on how to make the request."
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:157
msgid ""
"\"Do you need any special accommodations to help make your time at the "
"conference comfortable and productive? (e.g. accessibility considerations). "
"Please [email](mailto:contact@myconference.com) and include the details of "
"your request.\""
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:159
msgid "Demographic Info"
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:161
msgid ""
"‚úÖ If you do collect demographic info, be thoughtful about the structure of "
"the questions so that they are inclusive and don't contribute to alienating "
"or \"othering\" marginalized people."
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:164
msgid ""
"Not having an answer choice that matches your identity can be a very "
"alienating experience."
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:167
msgid ""
"‚úÖ Take anonymity and data security seriously. Have a plan for limiting "
"access to this information and keeping it secure."
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:169
msgid "Dietary Restrictions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:171
msgid ""
"üçé Ask for dietary restrictions on the registration form. Some people have "
"severe allergies or dietary restrictions that can affect their ability to "
"attend the conference."
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:173
msgid "Photo Policy"
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:175
msgid ""
"üçé If you will have a photographer at your event, include information for "
"attendees explaining that they may be photographed and how to opt out in the"
" registration form."
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:178
msgid ""
"(see lanyard/photography explanation under [Inclusive "
"Practices](11_inclusive_practices_during_checkin.md))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:180
msgid "Code of Conduct"
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:182
msgid ""
"üçé Show the text of the Code of Conduct and a required check-box that the "
"registrant has read it and agrees to abide by it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:184
msgid "[Childcare](06_childcare.md)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:186
msgid "‚úÖ Offer financial support for childcare."
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:188
msgid "Build it into your budget."
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:190
msgid ""
"Link it to sponsorships, or university partners, or make part of the "
"registration fee from all attendees go towards providing childcare support "
"as service."
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:191
msgid ""
"Add an option to the registration, e.g.: \"Donate $20 to help with childcare"
" costs.\""
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:192
msgid ""
"Collect the data on the registration form. How many people would make use of"
" childcare services or grants?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:194
msgid ""
"In general, the two major options are either to 1) award childcare grants "
"(people decide how to spend it, e.g. on their home babysitter) or 2) provide"
" on-site services."
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:197
msgid ""
"[Inclusive Practices During Check-"
"In](11_inclusive_practices_during_checkin.md)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:199
msgid "üçé Photography Permissions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:201
msgid "Managing photography opt-outs:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:204
msgid ""
"Badge lanyard at registration should be made available to indicate photo "
"preferences (green = photos fine; yellow = ask first; red = no photos)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:207
msgid "üçé Pronoun Pins, Buttons, or Ribbons"
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:209
msgid "Indicating pronouns:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:212
msgid ""
"Select a pin/button/ribbon for your lanyard to communicate your pronouns. "
"Using a pin even if you don't feel like you need one helps create a "
"welcoming space for attendees who do."
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:214
msgid ""
"Color-coordinate the pins by pronoun for quicker recognition and processing "
"by those who see the pins. This lowers the barrier to checking (look at the "
"color)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:217
msgid "[Grants/Scholarships](08_grants_scholarships.md)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:219
msgid "‚úÖ Offer grants to support attendance"
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:221
msgid "Eligibility Requirements"
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:224
msgid "Applicants should be"
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:227
msgid ""
"from a traditionally underrepresented and/or marginalized group in the "
"technology and/or open source communities including, but not limited to: "
"persons identifying as LGBTQ, indigenous, women, persons of color, and/or "
"persons with disabilities"
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:229
msgid ""
"and be unable to attend without some financial assistance. (language adapted"
" from [The Linux Foundation](https://www.linuxfoundation.org/event/api-"
"strategy-practice-conference-2017/diversity-scholarship/))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:231
msgid "Payment"
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:234
msgid ""
"Typically, recipients either submit receipts for reimbursement, have direct "
"expenses paid for by the organizing committee, or are granted a lump sum up-"
"front."
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:236
msgid ""
"We encourage conferences to pay for things directly rather than making "
"attendees pay and wait to be reimbursed, or at least offer this as an option"
" for people who want to use it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:239
msgid ""
"Waiting for reimbursement can be a financial burden on scholarship "
"recipients."
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:241
msgid "[Assessment of the event](12_assessment.md)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:243
msgid ""
"‚úÖ Survey participants after the event to establish whether your diversity "
"and inclusion measures had an effect."
msgstr ""

#: ../../02_minimal_measures.md:245
msgid ""
"See whether there is any correlation between being part of a minority group "
"and how welcoming the conference felt to the individual participants. You "
"can consider specifically asking about inclusion/diversity on the survey."
msgstr ""
